s.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040987,0.075648,0.093058,0.12268,0.10889,0.10749,0.10422,0.093981,0.080026,0.06761,0.057816,0.047595],"unified_progress":[0.039412,0.073389,0.090328,0.10948,0.10551,0.10301,0.098704,0.092935,0.090818,0.076657,0.06382,0.055929]},{"section":6,"text":"Wrinkled nuclei and halos are red flags for certain types of cervical changes.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047047,0.061186,0.077577,0.090566,0.10106,0.10509,0.10608,0.10256,0.095183,0.083099,0.0697,0.060854],"unified_progress":[0.042139,0.06366,0.081792,0.093222,0.098517,0.11307,0.10255,0.09791,0.092788,0.085608,0.071231,0.057509]},{"section":7,"text":"Also, these cells involve the full thickness of the squamous epithelium, which suggests it's not just a surface issue but deeper in the tissue.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041336,0.062057,0.079444,0.094296,0.10114,0.10565,0.10712,0.10264,0.093441,0.082569,0.071314,0.058997],"unified_progress":[0.039821,0.066098,0.083624,0.095432,0.1015,0.10321,0.10139,0.097862,0.096573,0.085752,0.071314,0.057424]},{"section":8,"text":"The basement membrane is intact, so that probably rules out something like invasive cancer where the basement membrane might be broken down.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035306,0.055698,0.076873,0.090672,0.099073,0.10446,0.10638,0.10465,0.09871,0.09038,0.07948,0.058323],"unified_progress":[0.035036,0.061105,0.078941,0.090374,0.099322,0.10093,0.10194,0.10149,0.10043,0.095749,0.077616,0.057062]},{"section":9,"text":"Now, considering her age, 22, which is relatively young, it's less likely to be something like cervical cancer, which is more common in older women.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033139,0.059887,0.076386,0.083698,0.088389,0.093435,0.097651,0.10135,0.10221,0.1039,0.093459,0.066505],"unified_progress":[0.040142,0.065545,0.074987,0.08