":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.052011,0.095627,0.1118,0.11586,0.11411,0.10388,0.096643,0.082436,0.07157,0.059356,0.051572,0.045142],"unified_progress":[0.045771,0.087532,0.10573,0.11425,0.11664,0.10392,0.097301,0.085681,0.085834,0.064095,0.051697,0.041555]},{"section":4,"text":"Also, the basement membrane is intact.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039709,0.079232,0.10058,0.11114,0.11182,0.10631,0.1008,0.088891,0.079319,0.069861,0.060258,0.052085],"unified_progress":[0.040943,0.078701,0.097755,0.10964,0.11354,0.10394,0.10093,0.090958,0.088509,0.072201,0.056795,0.046093]},{"section":5,"text":"Hmm, I remember that in cervical pathology, the basement membrane being intact usually means it's a squamous lesion, not involving the deeper tissues.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034254,0.070989,0.089088,0.10198,0.10606,0.10496,0.10378,0.096029,0.088277,0.078716,0.06782,0.058055],"unified_progress":[0.035612,0.07287,0.092319,0.10629,0.10968,0.105,0.10221,0.094287,0.092155,0.077131,0.061987,0.050458]},{"section":6,"text":"So, the lesion is confined to the epithelium.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033392,0.068884,0.086669,0.10041,0.10565,0.10462,0.10482,0.095885,0.088531,0.078215,0.069675,0.063251],"unified_progress":[0.0337,0.071099,0.091331,0.10634,0.11092,0.10455,0.10213,0.094096,0.094592,0.075617,0.062222,0.053405]},{"section":7,"text":"Now, the cells are described as atypical with wrinkled nuclei and perinuclear halos.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034442,0.069718,0.085332,0.096386,0.10212,0.10168,0.10206,0.095496,0.08933,0.078996,0.074705,0.069737],"unified_progress":[0.042487,0.078767,0.09255,0.10257,0.10685,0.10135,0.099632,0.092998,0.091215,0.075453,0.062926,0.053202]},{"section":8,"text":"I think perinuclear halos are a sign of cellular atypia, which can be seen in various pre-cancerous conditions.","dimension":17,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033357,0.067606,0.0845,0.096947,0.099577,0.10031,0.10249,0.099766,0.093914,0.0852,0.073978,0.062355],"unified_progress":[0.032974,0.065585,0.085645,0.097431,0.10257,0.1068,0.10411,0.099188,0.095254,0.086775,0.070777,0.052897]},{"section":9,"text":"The loss of normal orientation suggests that the cells are not organized in their usual way, which could indicate some form of dysplasia.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035813,0.064219,0.080655,0.092611,0.098022,0.10014,0.10257,0.099848,0.095999,0.087608,0.077489,0.065023],"unified_progress":[0.03465,0.065182,0.083108,0.0942,0.10123,0.10295,0.1019,0.099624,0.097194,0.08892,0.074179,0.056859]},{"section":10,"text":"Dysplasia is when cells look abnormal but haven't invaded deeper layers, so it's a pre-cancerous change.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03559,0.063383,0.079295,0.091103,0.09742,0.099788,0.10397,0.10161,0.096844,0.088053,0.077432,0.065509],"unified_progress":[0.034513,0.065052,0.083932,0.095792,0.10231,0.10545,0.1031,0.099487,0.097319,0.086926,0.071651,0.054475]},{"section":11,"text":"The full thickness of the squamous epithelium being involved makes me think of something more severe than just mild dysplasia.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032057,0.058227,0.075611,0.087236,0.094071,0.097245,0.10067,0.099854,0.097661,0.093118,0.085945,0.078301],"unified_progress":[0.031173,0.059978,0.07794,0.089996,0.096805,0.10106,0.1003,0.099082,0.098326,0.091924,0.082013,0.07141]},{"section":12,"text":"Wait, there's a term called \"squamous intraepithelial lesion\" which includes both dysplasia and carcinoma in situ.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027673,0.054783,0.072162,0.084631,0.095152,0.10017,0.10614,0.10573,0.10166,0.095337,0.083872,0.072694],"unified_progress":[0.030575,0.060975,0.080348,0.093981,0.10017,0.10628,0.10339,0.10012,0.098261,0.089677,0.075428,0.060791]},{"section":13,"text":"Carcinoma in situ means the cancer is confined to the epithelium and hasn't invaded the basement membrane.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032306,0.05725,0.074134,0.087977,0.097402,0.10145,0.10734,0.10422,0.099411,0.089102,0.079595,0.069816],"unified_progress":[0.033377,0.065161,0.085163,0.099671,0.10539,0.10656,0.10315,0.097707,0.097361,0.08186,0.067973,0.056619]},{"section":14,"text":"Since the basement membrane is intact here, it's not invasive cancer yet.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030801,0.056056,0.073391,0.086114,0.095284,0.099237,0.10392,0.10274,0.10114,0.094195,0.084898,0.072216],"unified_progress":[0.033442,0.063882,0.082192,0.093894,0.10186,0.10324,0.10205,0.099388,0.098082,0.08918,0.073912,0.058881]},{"section":15,"text":"So, putting it all together: atypical cells with these features across the entire squamous layer, basement membrane intact.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031169,0.056706,0.071529,0.081071,0.087985,0.090585,0.093016,0.092675,0.091869,0.096326,0.098793,0.10827],"unified_progress":[0.031787,0.060068,0.074023,0.085071,0.090211,0.091042,0.09305,0.092754,0.096052,0.090523,0.094308,0.10111]},{"section":16,"text":"That sounds like high-grade squamous intraepithelial lesion (HSIL), which is a category that includes carcinoma in situ.","dimension":17,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028488,0.060895,0.075788,0.086793,0.089901,0.091888,0.096618,0.09697,0.094776,0.093589,0.091419,0.092874],"unified_progress":[0.026694,0.054738,0.072785,0.085529,0.091124,0.098696,0.098245,0.098432,0.098937,0.094498,0.091176,0.089145]},{"section":17,"text":"HSIL is more severe than low-grade and is associated with a higher risk of progression to invasive cancer.","dimension":13,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03663,0.053606,0.067625,0.077738,0.087759,0.093343,